About EZ Realty Accordion Module

This module shows the property listings in a vertical orientation content accordion. The accordion will cycle through each of the property listings automatically - and will slide each pane open. You're able to configure the EZ Realty Accordion Module to display images and information with a range of features such as:-

  • define the title source
  • define the descriptive text source, and how much to display
  • choose the image source - eg. thumbnail, main image or panorama image - as well as the width for that image
  • configure the display div height - which may be necessary depending on the size of images displayed, and the amount of descriptive text used.

When setting up the EZ Realty Accordion Module - select the type of listings you want to display by using the refinement filters - eg. the listing type, whether to refine by category, country, state, or suburb.

Common Questions about the EZ Realty Accordion Module

Q. What's the best module position to use for the accordion module?
A. Select a module position with sufficient display width across the page for what you're showing on the page. In most cases - a module position above or below the main page content is best - however you could use a sidebar position if just showing images in the accordion. It really depends - so take all of these things into consideration.

Q. Why don't I see anything - it's published?
A. Recheck your settings - and then check the listings you've created. After all - if you configure the module to use the panorama image - but havn't uploaded a panorama image for the property listings - then you won't see anything on the page output.

Q. It's not working - or it seems to be breaking my Joomla template menu. How do I fix it?
A. Test out the "Disable jQuery File" setting. You may need to enable it or disable it - depending on what you've already done to your site. Make sure you've unpublished other modules while testing this - so that you do not wrongly attribute the problem to the accordion module. Q. Why aren't all of the listings being displayed? I configured it to show 30 listings - but there are only 20 being displayed.

  • show images in a vertical or horizontal display - or in a multi-row/column output

  • add a configurable amount of descriptive text to the image
  • configurable image dimensions
  • delay image loading with the lazyloader system
  • use popup image previews

When setting up the EZ Realty Multidisplay Module - select the type of listings you want to display by using the refinement filters - eg. the listing type, whether to refine by category, country, state, or suburb.

Common Questions about the EZ Realty Multidisplay Module

Q. Why are the images running off the page?
A. Check how many listings you've configured to display - and also check the column count. The column count controls how many items are displayed across the page - so if you have a narrow module position and a big column count - then you may need to change the column count to 1.

Q. I don't see any listings?
A. If you've used the refinement filters to display a certain type of listing - make sure you actually have some listings that meet the specified parameters.

Q. I don't see any images! What's wrong?
A. Check which image source you're using. If you've configured the multidisplay module to use the panorama image - make sure you've uploaded an image in the panorama image field for at least 1 property listing. The panorama image field is on the resource tab of the add/edit property details form.

Q. The panorama image upload field isn't where you said it would be.
A. Make sure you've enabled use of the panorama image upload field in the EZ Realty configuration settings.

Q. Where do I find the EZ Realty configuration settings?

Q. It's not working - or it seems to be breaking my Joomla template menu. How do I fix it?
A. Test out the "Disable jQuery File" setting or the LazyLoader setting. You may need to enable or disable both or a combination of them - depending on what you've already done to your site. Make sure you've unpublished other modules while testing this - so that you do not wrongly attribute the problem to the Multidisplay module.
